# Load ITS2 data

Model

library(dplyr)
library(rstatix)

# Run Kruskal-Wallis tests
kruskal_list <- list(
  dat1 = kruskal.test(Distance ~ Group, dat1), # bacteria jac
  dat2 = kruskal.test(Distance ~ Group, dat2), # bacteria bray
  dat3 = kruskal.test(Distance ~ Group, dat3), # fungi jac
  dat4 = kruskal.test(Distance ~ Group, dat4)  # fungi bray
)

# Coerce to a summary data frame
kruskal_summary <- bind_rows(lapply(names(kruskal_list), function(name) {
  res <- kruskal_list[[name]]
  data.frame(
    dataset = name,
    statistic = unname(res$statistic),
    parameter = unname(res$parameter),
    p_value = res$p.value,
    method = res$method,
    stringsAsFactors = FALSE
  )
}))

# run pairwise Wilcoxon test for dat3 as it was significant
pairwise_wilcox <- dat3 %>%
  pairwise_wilcox_test(Distance ~ Group) %>%
  mutate(dataset = "dat3") %>%
  select(dataset, group1, group2, p, p.adj, p.adj.signif)

kruskal_summary
pairwise_wilcox
# Write results to file
write.table(kruskal_summary, file = "firstdistances_kruskal_results.txt", sep = "\t", row.names = FALSE)
write.table(pairwise_wilcox, file = "firstdistances_pairwise_wilcox_fungijaccard.txt", sep = "\t", row.names = FALSE)
